		"startIntroPart1": "All hail the Keeper of the Archive, guardian of what remains of human knowledge! When the bombs fell and the networks died, it was your people who risked everything to salvage the servers, the hard drives, the printed texts from the burning libraries. In the ashes of the old world, the Archive rose as a fortress of memory, cataloguing every surviving fragment of science, engineering, and medicine. Where others hoarded bullets, you hoarded blueprints. Where others built walls, you built databases.",
